==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Augite
<hw>Au"gite</hw> <pr>(⟦add⟧"j⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>augites</ets>, Gr. <grk>a'ygi`ths</grk>, fr. <grk>a'ygh`</grk>
brightness: cf. F. <ets>augite</ets>.]</ety> <def>A variety of pyroxene,
usually of a black or dark green color, occurring in igneous rocks, such
as basalt; -- also used instead of the general term
<isa>pyroxene</isa>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Augitic</ent>⟦br⟧
